{
  "name": "PrivacyBenchHIPAA",
  "version": "0.1",
  "description": "HIPAA Limited Data Set (§164.514(e)(2)) compliance benchmark for PII redaction filters. Tests the 16 LDS identifier categories that must be removed AND the 'retained' carve-outs (city/state/ZIP, dates, ages, larger-than-street geographic) that must NOT be removed. Unlike PrivacyBench (which tests subjective PII-association judgement), this benchmark is wooden: every email is PHI, every phone is PHI, every name is PHI — definitional, not contextual. Designed to score a true HIPAA filter at >=99%.",
  "scoring": "Per-question: 5 = perfect (all PHI removed with right LDS class, all retained signals preserved). 4 = all PHI removed but 1 class miscategorized OR 1 retained signal over-redacted. 3 = all PHI removed but >=2 issues. 2 = >=1 PHI missed (HIPAA violation). 1 = >=2 PHI missed. 0 = catastrophic.",
